        <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The ideal timing for <a href="/blog/post-workout-recovery" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">post-workout cold therapy</a> is within 15-30 minutes after exercise, when inflammation and muscle damage are beginning to peak. A 3-5 minute cold plunge can significantly reduce next-day soreness and improve subsequent training quality.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
          <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-green-800 mb-3">Optimal Recovery Protocol:</h3>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-green-700">
            <li>Complete your workout and cool down briefly (5-10 minutes)</li>
            <li>Enter cold water (50-59°F) for 3-5 minutes</li>
            <li>Focus on controlled breathing</li>
            <li>Warm up gradually after exiting</li>
            <li>Hydrate and refuel with proper nutrition</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-xl text-gray-800 mb-4">Seasonal Training Support</h3>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
